<item>
            <title>[OAK-4116] Broadcasting cache: disabled by default</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-4116</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The broadcasting cache is now enabled by default, but I suggest we disable it again until we have more data, because:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It does a (although very limited) port scan trying to connect to other instances that are also connected (stored in MongoDB / the database).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We don&apos;t know the performance impact yet (we do have some data that show it&apos;s good, but we have very limited data so far).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</description>
